<br>
I guess that's what we get for $10/month though.<br>
<br>
The idea of using volunteer support for your company's CS is mind-bogglingly stupid.  Can you imagine if another company did that?  My company handles data storage, I can just imagine volunteer &quot;guides&quot; hired to do our CS.<br>
<br>
Customer: &quot;Your program screwed up and I lost a lot of data!&quot;<br>
Guide: &quot;Is your data still being lost?&quot;<br>
Customer: &quot;WTF does that matter!  I need my data back!&quot;<br>
Guide: &quot;I'm sorry, I can't verify that you've lost data.  Let me know if it happens again.&quot;<br>
Customer: &quot;And then you'll restore it?&quot;<br>
Guide: &quot;No, but I'll make a note of it in my report.&quot;<br>
Customer: &quot;And then someone else will restore my data?&quot;<br>
Guide: &quot;No, but the bug might get fixed eventually.&quot;<br>
<br>
I still crash sometimes when zoning from OOT to EFP on the boat.  By the time I get back on, I'm zoning back to OOT.  Horribly frustrating, but the guides just blow me off.  One time I asked if they would just do &quot;who all grumples&quot; a few times as I zone, and if I crash again, would they please teleport me to EFP.  The answer was &quot;no&quot;.  Nothing like a 90 minute boat ride to get a fellow's dander up.<br>
