<br>
In another thread Galadriel stated what I feel may be the real reason nothing has happened to our class.  Because the complaining other paying customers playing their classes would make.  If they fixed pet melee, mage nukes, etc we would have large numbers of melee and casters crying foul.<br>
<br>
So I'm sure verant looks at the situation and says &quot;why should we spend time/money fixing something that will please 2% of our player base and anger 30%?  Even if we are right, there are alot more paying customers that would not want us restored to our pre-expansion power.<br>
<br>
Sadly, canceling accounts may indeed be the only way to get their attention.  I have often thought that if all mages on all servers stood together and canceled accounts until it was fixed, we might get something done.  But on every rant/flame/discussion about broken mechanics on these boards there is always somebody that is either A. Unwilling to see the negative side of mages, or B. totally ignorant of what so many of us are talking about.  Those people always argue we are not broken and label the rest whiners.<br>
<br>
If we were going to cancel accounts and stand together, it would have to be all of us, or at least enough that nearly no high level mages exist on any server.<br>
<br>
Many of you know me from my posts, I have been active on this site for a very long time.  I have loved my mage for over 2 years now, but I will cancel my account with the rest of you if it will make verant finally take notice and fix us.  Even if it means losing my mage forever, it's a cause I believe in.<br>
<br>
